.ident	"@(#)proto:locale/C/menus/help/datetime	1.8"
.related kbhelp genhelp help.main
.title Help: View or Change Time and Date
ABOUT THIS OPTION
Select the View or Change Time and Date option to check that the
current time and date are set on your computer and to change
them if necessary.  You can also select the appropriate timezone.

CHANGING THE DATE AND TIME
Use the <Tab> or arrow keys to move to the field (Year, Month,
Day, Hour, or Minute) that you want to change; then type the
correct information.

CHANGING THE TIMEZONE
Use the <Tab> or arrow keys to move to the Timezone field, then
press <F2>.  A list of continents appears.  An asterisk (*)
is displayed next to the continent where the current timezone
resides.
                                   (CONTINUED)
.page
To change the continent, use the <Tab> or arrow keys to move
the asterisk to the appropriate field; then press <Enter>.
A list of timezone choices appears.  An asterisk (*) is
displayed next to the current timezone.

To change the timezone, use the <Tab> or arrow keys to move
the asterisk to the appropriate field; then press <Enter>.

EXITING THE DATE AND TIME FORM
Press <F10> to enter your changes and exit the Date and Time
menu.

EXITING HELP
Press <Esc> to return to the Verify Date and Time menu.
Press <F1> for more help.
